        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I saw my pet at more less half health, so I decided to cast a ShadowBond on him. I saw his HP bar rasing and raising almost to full. I was alone, and no one apart from me healed him. I was like WTF is going on here. So I repeated the experiment, this time taking a log:</P><P>-------------------------<BR>[Thu Jan 03 14:45:29 2002] Logging to 'eqlog.txt' is now *ON*.<BR>[Thu Jan 03 14:45:37 2002] I have 51 percent of my hit points left.<BR>[Thu Jan 03 14:45:42 2002] You begin casting Shadowbond.<BR>[Thu Jan 03 14:45:44 2002] Xann pulses with a blue-green aura.<BR>[Thu Jan 03 14:45:44 2002] You beam a smile at Xann.<BR>[Thu Jan 03 14:45:44 2002] You say, 'Ahhh, I feel much better now...'<BR>[Thu Jan 03 14:46:08 2002] Your pact fades.<BR>[Thu Jan 03 14:46:09 2002] Your pet's Shadowbond spell has worn off.<BR>[Thu Jan 03 14:46:15 2002] I have 86 percent of my hit points left.<BR>-------------------------</P><P>So, a 500 HP pact healed him from 51% to 86% of his life. That means a 35% healing up. If 35% = 500 hp, then 100% is not even 1500 hp.</P><P>I thought our spectre pet health range was from 2400 to 2700 hp, depending on the summon level.</P><P>Questions: </P><P>- Does our 54 pact actually heal far more than 500 hp?</P><P>- Does out 59 pet have far less HP than originally thought?</P><P>- Does our 59 pet regen HP like crazy? If we assume that 54 pact is 500 hp heal and spectre pet has around 2500 hp, then the spectre's HP regen rate considering the log above mentioned is over 100 hp per tick standing up, which is hard to believe.</P><P>Anyone got the answer?</P><P>Yaguex, warlock, Paradigm, Solusek Ro, retired.</font></td>
