        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">From many tests with checking % health and damage to my pet, I have concluded that the 56, 61 hitter monk pet has 1500 hps.  </P><P>The top spectre pet has around 2350 hps, if my friends tests were accurate.  Pets up to level 56 regen 30hp/tick.  Not sure about the spec, don't have it yet.</P><P>Add the pets regen to what you healed and you get this formula.</P><P>There were almost 7 ticks from when you asked pet health the first time to the second time.  If you just caught him befor the tick then thats 7 ticks of regen.</P><P>500(shadowbond)+210(7 30hp regen ticks)=710 hps in that time. So that is 710 hps healed really.</P><P>710*3~2100 hps.  This assumes the spec pet only has a regen of 30/tick like other pets and did NOT have any regen on him like chloro etc.  If this was a lower hitting spec pet, then the focused pet 59 hitter pet would have 2300+ hps :).</P><P></P><P></P><P><BR>Edited by - Rekcim on 01/04/2002  08:50:06</P><P>Edited by - Rekcim on 01/04/2002  08:55:50</P><P>Edited by - Rekcim on 01/04/2002  08:56:49</P><P>Edited by - Rekcim on 01/04/2002  08:59:07<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
